                            <comment id="13107511" author="brian.stansberry" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2015 12:38:54 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m scheduling this for 3 as AFAIK it&apos;s not blocking anything required for 2 and it won&apos;t make 2.0.0.CR1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13325963" author="luck3y" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2016 15:27:16 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Note, this is mostly fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-1977&quot; title=&quot;Embedded Server ignores system properties when starting.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFCORE-1977&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFCORE-1977&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, however, starting an embedded server does not currently override configured logging properties correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that in, for example the manualmode unit tests, standalone servers that are started, then stopped will persist a hardcoded path to a logfile that will then be picked up by the embedded server when starting and logged to.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13326000" author="luck3y" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2016 19:04:20 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-1187&quot; title=&quot;Embedded server start / stop / start with new --jboss-home continues to refer to previous server.log&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFCORE-1187&quot;&gt;WFCORE-1187&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-1829&quot; title=&quot;Allow server to start in suspended mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFCORE-1829&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFCORE-1829&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the issues tracking this. Closing this as a duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
